defaultColumnWidths.name: defaultColumnWidths
defaultColumnWidths.short_desc:
How wide is a default column for a given default font and size?
Empirical data found by inspecting real Excel files and reading off the pixel width
in Microsoft Office Excel 2007.

setTrueTypeFontPath.name: setTrueTypeFontPath
setTrueTypeFontPath.short_desc: Set the path to the folder containing .ttf files. There should be a trailing slash.
setTrueTypeFontPath.long_desc:
Typical locations on variout some platforms:
  • C:/Windows/Fonts/
  • /usr/share/fonts/truetype/
  • ~/.fonts/

getTrueTypeFontPath.name: getTrueTypeFontPath
getTrueTypeFontPath.short_desc: Get the path to the folder containing .ttf files.

calculateColumnWidth.name: calculateColumnWidth
calculateColumnWidth.short_desc: Calculate an (approximate) OpenXML column width, based on font size and text contained

getTextWidthPixelsExact.name: getTextWidthPixelsExact
getTextWidthPixelsExact.short_desc: Get GD text width in pixels for a string of text in a certain font at a certain rotation angle

getTextWidthPixelsApprox.name: getTextWidthPixelsApprox
getTextWidthPixelsApprox.short_desc: Get approximate width in pixels for a string of text in a certain font at a certain rotation angle
getTextWidthPixelsApprox.hint_desc: Text width in pixels (no padding added)

fontSizeToPixels.name: fontSizeToPixels
fontSizeToPixels.short_desc: Calculate an (approximate) pixel size, based on a font points size

inchSizeToPixels.name: inchSizeToPixels
inchSizeToPixels.short_desc: Calculate an (approximate) pixel size, based on inch size

centimeterSizeToPixels.name: centimeterSizeToPixels
centimeterSizeToPixels.short_desc: Calculate an (approximate) pixel size, based on centimeter size

getTrueTypeFontFileFromFont.name: getTrueTypeFontFileFromFont
getTrueTypeFontFileFromFont.short_desc: Returns the font path given the font
errors: The "font" parameter of the method "getTrueTypeFontFileFromFont" is missing a @param tag

getCharsetFromFontName.name: getCharsetFromFontName
getCharsetFromFontName.short_desc: Returns the associated charset for the font name.

getDefaultColumnWidthByFont.name: getDefaultColumnWidthByFont
getDefaultColumnWidthByFont.short_desc:
Get the effective column width for columns without a column dimension or column with width -1
For example, for Calibri 11 this is 9.140625 (64 px)

pPixels.name: pPixels
pPixels.short_desc: true = return column width in pixels, false = return in OOXML units

getDefaultRowHeightByFont.name: getDefaultRowHeightByFont
getDefaultRowHeightByFont.short_desc:
Get the effective row height for rows without a row dimension or rows with height -1
For example, for Calibri 11 this is 15 points

CHARSET_ANSI_LATIN.name: CHARSET_ANSI_LATIN
CHARSET_ANSI_LATIN.short_desc: Character set codes used by BIFF5-8 in Font records
